Rooms.Name: The Reading Room
Rooms.Description:
You are in a small, simple room which is mostly empty, save a few
wooden desks and benches.  To the east you hear the bustle of the Temple
of Midgaard, a sharp contrast to the relative quiet of this peaceful
room.

Rooms.Name: The Temple Of Midgaard
Rooms.Description:
You are in the southern end of the temple hall in the Temple of Midgaard.
The temple has been constructed from giant marble blocks, eternal in
appearance, and most of the walls are covered by ancient wall paintings
picturing Gods, giants and peasants.
   Large steps lead down through the grand temple gate, descending the huge
mound upon which the temple is built and ends on the temple square below.
To the west, you see the Reading Room.  The donation room is in a small
alcove to your east.

Rooms.Name: The Clerics' Inner Sanctum
Rooms.Description:
This is the inner sanctum.  A picture of the mighty Thor, is hanging on
the wall, just above the altar which is set against the western wall.  A well
in the middle of the floor leads down into darkness.  Vile smells waft from
the depths.

Rooms.Name: The Bar Of Divination
Rooms.Description:
The bar is one of the finest in the land, lucky it is members only.  Fine
furniture is set all around the room.  A small sign is hanging on the wall.

Rooms.Name: The Entrance To The Clerics' Guild
Rooms.Description:
The entrance hall is a small modest room, reflecting the true nature of
the Clerics.  The exit leads east to the temple square.  A small entrance to
the bar is in the northern wall.

Rooms.Name: The Temple Square
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on the temple square.  Huge marble steps lead up to the
temple gate.  The entrance to the Clerics' Guild is to the west, and the old
Grunting Boar Inn, is to the east.  Just south of here you see the market
square, the center of Midgaard.

Rooms.Name: The Entrance Hall Of The Grunting Boar Inn
Rooms.Description:
You are standing in the entrance hall of the Grunting Boar Inn.  The hall
has been wisely decorated with simple, functional furniture.  The heavy smell
of dust and aging paper drifts in from the Post Office to the north.  A small
staircase leads up to the reception and the bar is to the east.

Rooms.Name: The Grunting Boar
Rooms.Description:
You are standing in the bar.  The bar is set against the northern wall, old
archaic writing, carvings and symbols cover its top.  A fireplace is built into
the western wall, and through the southeastern windows you can see the temple
square.  This place makes you feel like home.
A small sign with big letters is fastened to the bar.

Rooms.Name: The Reception
Rooms.Description:
You are standing in the reception.  The staircase leads down to the
entrance hall.  An exit to the north leads to the Cryogenic Center.
There is a small sign on the counter.

Rooms.Name: The Bakery
Rooms.Description:
You are standing inside the small bakery.  A sweet scent of danish and
fine bread fills the room.  The bread and Danish are arranged in fine order
on the shelves, and seem to be of the finest quality.
A small sign is on the counter.

Rooms.Name: The General Store
Rooms.Description:
You are inside the general store.  All sorts of items are stacked on shelves
behind the counter, safely out of your reach.
A small note hangs on the wall.

Rooms.Name: The Weapon Shop
Rooms.Description:
The smell of worked metals and various quenching oils fills the room.  Every
available space in the room including the ceiling is loaded with various
equipment and weaponry.  There is a small note on the counter.

Rooms.Name: Main Street
Rooms.Description:
You are at the end of the main street of Midgaard.  South of here is the
entrance to the Guild of Magic Users.  The street continues east towards the
market square.  The magic shop is to the north and to the west is the city
gate.

Rooms.Name: Main Street
Rooms.Description:
You are on the main street passing through the City of Midgaard.  South of
here is the entrance to the Armory, and the bakery is to the north.  East of
here is the market square.

Rooms.Name: Market Square
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on the market square, the famous Square of Midgaard.
A large, peculiar looking statue is standing in the middle of the square.
Roads lead in every direction, north to the temple square, south to the
common square, east and westbound is the main street.

Rooms.Name: Main Street
Rooms.Description:
You are on the main street crossing through town.  To the north is the
general store, and the main street continues east.  To the west you see and
hear the market place, to the south a small door leads into the Pet Shop.

Rooms.Name: Main Street
Rooms.Description:
The main street, to the north is the weapon shop and to the south is the
Guild of Swordsmen.  To the east you leave town and to the west the street
leads to the market square.

Rooms.Name: The Entrance To The Mages' Guild
Rooms.Description: The entrance hall to this guild is a small, poor lighted room.

Rooms.Name: The Mages' Bar
Rooms.Description:
The bar is one of the weirdest in the land.  Mystical images float around
the air.  Illusions of fine furniture appear all around the room.

Rooms.Name: The Mages' Laboratory
Rooms.Description:
This is the Magical Experiments Laboratory.  Dark smoke-stained stones arch
over numerous huge oaken tables, most of these cluttered with strange- looking
pipes and flasks.  The floor is covered with half-erased pentagrams and even
weirder symbols, and a blackboard in a dark corner has only been partially
cleaned, some painful-looking letters faintly visible.

Rooms.Name: The Armory
Rooms.Description:
The armory has a wide assortment of armor displayed on the walls and in the
windows. Helmets, shields, and suits of armor are for sale. To the north is
the main street. On the wall is a small note.

Rooms.Name: The Entrance Hall To The Guild Of Swordsmen
Rooms.Description:
The entrance hall to the Guild of Swordsmen.  A place where one has to be
careful not to say something wrong (or right).  To the east is the bar and to
the north is the main street.

Rooms.Name: The Bar Of Swordsmen
Rooms.Description:
The bar of swordsmen, once upon a time beautifully furnished.  But now the
furniture is all around you in small pieces.  To the south is the yard, and
to the west is the entrance hall.

Rooms.Name: The Tournament And Practice Yard
Rooms.Description:
This is the practice yard of the fighters.  To the north is the bar.
A well leads down into darkness.

Rooms.Name: The Eastern End Of Poor Alley
Rooms.Description:
You are at the poor alley.  South of here is the Grubby Inn and to the
east you see common square.  The alley continues further west.

Rooms.Name: The Common Square
Rooms.Description:
The common square, people pass you, talking to each other.  To the west is
the poor alley and to the east is the dark alley.  To the north, this square
is connected to the market square.  From the south you notice a nasty smell.

Rooms.Name: The Dark Alley
Rooms.Description:
The dark alley, to the west is the common square and to the south is the
Guild of Thieves.  The alley continues east.

Rooms.Name: The Entrance Hall To The Guild Of Thieves
Rooms.Description:
The entrance hall to the thieves' and assassins' guild.  A place where you
can lose both your life and your money, if you are not careful.  To the north
is the dark alley and to the east is the thieves' bar.

Rooms.Name: The Thieves' Bar
Rooms.Description:
The bar of the thieves.  Once upon a time this place was beautifully
furnished, but now it seems almost empty.  To the south is the yard, and to
the west is the entrance hall.
   (Maybe the furniture has been stolen?!)

Rooms.Name: The Secret Yard
Rooms.Description:
The secret practice yard of thieves and assassins.  To the north is the
bar.  A well leads down into darkness.

Rooms.Name: The Dump
Rooms.Description:
The dump, where the people from the city drop their garbage.  Through the
garbage you can see a large junction of pipes, looks like the entrance to the
sewer system.  North of here you see the common square.

Rooms.Name: The Pet Shop
Rooms.Description:
The Pet Shop is a small crowded store, full of cages and animals of
various sizes.  There is a sign on the wall.

Rooms.Name: PETSHOP STOREROOM
Rooms.Description:
Make two rooms and some pets.  The rooms MUST be sequential.  If the first
room is 315 then the second must be 316.  The second room is known as the
storeroom.  All that is required in the storeroom is to load one of each mob you
wish to be a pet.  This room can not have any exits and will never be used by
mortals.  Although a pet shopkeeper is not required it is recommended.  After
all of this is done ask your coder to implement the petshop.  It will not work
until the code is changed and the MUD is rebooted.  The cost of pets is 300
times their level.

Rooms.Name: The Magic Shop
Rooms.Description:
Behind the counter you see various items, neatly placed in racks,
presumably most of them are magic.

Rooms.Name: Inside The West Gate Of Midgaard
Rooms.Description:
You are by two small towers that have been built into the city wall and
connected with a footbridge across the heavy wooden gate.  Main Street leads
east and Wall Road leads south from here.

Rooms.Name: Inside The East Gate Of Midgaard
Rooms.Description:
You are by two small towers that have been built into the city wall and
connected with a footbridge across the heavy wooden gate.  Main Street leads
west from here.  To the south you see the Water Shop.

Rooms.Name: Wall Road
Rooms.Description:
You are walking next to the western city wall.  The road continues further
south and the city gate is just north of here.

Rooms.Name: Wall Road
Rooms.Description:
You are walking next to the western city wall.  Wall Road continues further
north and south.  A small, poor alley leads east.
Some letters have been written on the wall here.

Rooms.Name: Poor Alley
Rooms.Description:
You are on Poor Alley, which continues further east.  You see the
city wall to the west.

Rooms.Name: The Dark Alley At The Levee
Rooms.Description:
You are standing in the alley which continues east and west.  South of
here you see the levee.

Rooms.Name: The Eastern End Of The Alley
Rooms.Description:
You are standing at the eastern end of the alley, the city wall is just
east, blocking any further movement.  A small warehouse is directly south of
here.

Rooms.Name: Wall Road
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on the road next to the western city wall, which
continues north.  South of here is a bridge across the river.

Rooms.Name: Grubby Inn
Rooms.Description:
You are inside the old Grubby Inn.  This place has not been cleaned for
several decades; vile smells make you dizzy.

Rooms.Name: The Levee
Rooms.Description:
You are at the levee.  South of here you see the river gently flowing west.
The river bank is very low making it possible to enter the river.

Rooms.Name: The Deserted Warehouse
Rooms.Description:
You are inside the warehouse.  The room is decorated with various old
items from ships.

Rooms.Name: On The Bridge
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on the stone bridge crosses the river.  The bridge is
built out from the western city wall and the river flows west through an
opening in the wall ten feet below the bridge.

Rooms.Name: Outside The West Gate Of Midgaard
Rooms.Description:
You are by two small towers that have been built into the city wall and
connected with a footbridge across the heavy wooden gate.  To the west you
can see the edge of a big forest.

Rooms.Name: Outside The East Gate Of Midgaard
Rooms.Description:
You are by two small towers that have been built into the city wall and
connected with a footbridge across the heavy wooden gate.  To the east the
plains stretch out in the distance.

Rooms.Name: By The Temple Altar
Rooms.Description:
You are by the temple altar in the northern end of the Temple of Midgaard.
A huge altar made from white polished marble dominates this part of the temple.
Towering behind the altar is a ten foot tall sitting statue of Odin, the King of
the Gods. To the north, steps lead out the back of the temple towards the
countryside.

Rooms.Name: Ye Olde Water Shoppe
Rooms.Description:
You are standing in the center of a small wooden shop whose walls are
covered with racks upon racks of water jugs.  Several large barrels with
spigots are stacked in the corner.

Rooms.Name: Behind The Temple Altar
Rooms.Description:
You are on a dirt path leading away from the Temple Altar which is south
of here.  To the north, the path continues through the lush contryside of
Midgaard towards the Dragonhelm Mountains far off to the north.

Rooms.Name: The Great Field Of Midgaard
Rooms.Description:
You are walking on a wide dirt path through the lush, green, fresh
Midgaard countryside.  You can see to the horizon to the north, east,
and west; the busy city of Midgaard lies to the south.  All around you
is healthy green grass and an occasional large oak tree.  The sun feels
wonderful on your face and a pleasant wind blows through your hair.  Birds
chirp quietly to themselves and you can smell the faint scent of flowers
and freshly cut grass.  You feel like you could lie down in the grass and
stay here forever, surrounded by powerful beauty in all directions.
   The path you are on continues north through the field and south back
to Midgaard.

Rooms.Name: The Great Field Of Midgaard
Rooms.Description:
You are walking on a wide dirt path through the lush, green, fresh
Midgaard countryside.  You can see to the horizon to the north, east,
and west; the busy city of Midgaard lies to the south.  All around you
is healthy green grass and an occasional large oak tree.  The sun feels
wonderful on your face and a pleasant wind blows through your hair.  Birds
chirp quietly to themselves and you can smell the faint scent of flowers
and freshly cut grass.  You feel like you could lie down in the grass and
stay here forever, surrounded by powerful beauty in all directions.
   There is a strange structure on the eastern side of the path.  A small
dirt path splits off of the main path and leads off to the west.

Rooms.Name: The Post Office
Rooms.Description:
You are in the central post office for Midgaard.  Piles of assorted mail
lay untouched in the corners, collecting cobwebs.  Several large crates have
been pried open by curious customs agents, and are now stacked along the west
wall, hiding plenty of 'WANTED' posters.
There is a sign posted on the wall here.

Rooms.Name: The Midgaard Donation Room
Rooms.Description:
You are in a small, undecorated room just off of the main temple.  There
are a couple of small wooden benches here where people occasionally sit
while they wait for items to appear.  The temple is to the west.

Rooms.Name: The Cryogenic Center
Rooms.Description:
You are standing in an impossibly white sterile room with cylindrical
body-length canisters lined up against the walls.  The Reception is to the
south.

Rooms.Name: The Great Field Of Midgaard
Rooms.Description:
You are walking on a wide dirt path through the lush, green, fresh
Midgaard countryside.  You can see to the horizon to the north, east,
and west; the busy city of Midgaard lies to the south.  All around you
is healthy green grass and an occasional large oak tree.  The sun feels
wonderful on your face and a pleasant wind blows through your hair.  Birds
chirp quietly to themselves and you can smell the faint scent of flowers
and freshly cut grass.  You feel like you could lie down in the grass and
stay here forever, surrounded by powerful beauty in all directions.
   The way north appears to be blocked by a large plot device and you cannot
see any way around it.

Rooms.Name: The Dirt Path
Rooms.Description:
You are walking along a narrow dirt path through the lush, green,
fresh Midgaard countryside.  You can see to the horizon to the north
and east; the busy city of Midgaard lies to the south.  All around
you is healthy green grass and an occasional large oak tree.  The sun
feels wonderful on your face and a pleasant wind blows through your
hair.  Birds chirp quietly to themselves and you can smell the faint
scent of flowers and freshly cut grass.  You feel like you could lie
down in the grass and stay here forever, surrounded by powerful beauty
in all directions.
   There is a large rusty gate sitting in a stone archway just to the
west.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A wizard walks around behind the counter, talking to himself.
Mobiles.Description:
The wizard looks old and senile, and yet he looks like a very powerful
wizard.  He is equipped with fine clothing, and is wearing many fine rings and
bracelets.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The baker looks at you calmly, wiping flour from his face with one hand.
Mobiles.Description:
A fat, nice looking baker.  But you can see that he has many scars on his
body.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A grocer stands at the counter, with a slightly impatient look on his face.
Mobiles.Description: A tall grocer, who moves two 200 pounds bag of flour around on his shoulders.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A weaponsmith is standing here.
Mobiles.Description:
He is a young weaponsmith, who still has lots to learn but he is still eager
to sell you his latest implements of carnage and destruction.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An armorer stands here displaying his new (and previously owned) armors.
Mobiles.Description:
An old but very strong armorer.  He has made more suits of armor in his
life than you have ever seen.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A receptionist is standing behind the counter here, smiling at you.
Mobiles.Description:
You notice a tired look in her face.  She looks like she isn't paid well
enough to put up with any crap from mud players with attitudes.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A retired captain stands here, selling boats.
Mobiles.Description: This captain has eaten more sharks than you have killed peas.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A sailor stands here, waiting to help you.
Mobiles.Description: He looks like a strong, fit sailor.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Uncle Juan is here ready to take your order.
Mobiles.Description: He looks like he may or may not have a green card.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Wally the Watermaster is standing behind the counter.
Mobiles.Description:
Wally is a bit pudgy but looks very strong.  He has a glass of Midgaard
Natural Spring Water in his hand.  When he notices you, he proudly displays his
fine collection of contemporary waters.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The head postmaster is standing here, waiting to help you with your mail.
Mobiles.Description:
The Postmaster seems like a happy old man, though a bit sluggish.  He worries
about the reputation of the MMS (Midgaard Mail Service), as many people seem to
think that it is slow.  Perhaps if he were to brush the cobwebs from his uniform
it would help to make a better impression.

Mobiles.LongDescription: This saleswoman is laden with gadgets and gizmos that are outrageously priced.
Mobiles.Description:
A combination of good business sense, charming personality, and good looks
has made her a success at pushing useless products on uneducated buyers.  Only
on a rare occasion does she sell anything useful.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A very kind and caring soul is here looking out for those who need it.
Mobiles.Description:
She immediately reminds you of your mother.  Constantly worrying about
everyone and everything.  She is always around to help out those who have hit
hard times and need a little boost.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A newbie tour guide is here to help. "@RTell guide help@y" for assistance.@n
Mobiles.Description:
This young lady has the sole purpose of helping those who need assistance.
She will follow you around Midgaard and provide a walking tour of the local
attractions.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Your guildmaster is studying a spellbook while preparing to cast a spell.
Mobiles.Description:
Even though your guildmaster looks old and tired, you can clearly see the
vast amount of knowledge she possesses.  She is wearing fine magic clothing, and
you notice that she is surrounded by a blue shimmering aura.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Your guildmaster is praying to your God here.
Mobiles.Description:
You are in no doubt that this guildmaster is truly close to your God; he has
a peaceful, loving look.  You notice that he is surrounded by a white aura.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beggar is sitting here, could she be a guildmaster?
Mobiles.Description:
You realize that whenever your guildmaster moves, you fail to notice it - the
way of the true thief.  She is to be dressed in poor clothing, having the
appearance of a beggar.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Your guildmaster is standing here sharpening an axe.
Mobiles.Description:
This is your master.  Big and strong with bulging muscles.  Several scars
across his body proves that he was using arms before you were born.  He has a
calm look on his face.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A sorcerer is guarding the entrance.
Mobiles.Description:
He is an experienced mage who has specialized in the field of Combat Magic.
He is here to guard the Mage's Guild and his superior knowledge of offensive as
well as defensive spells make him a deadly opponent.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A knight templar is guarding the entrance.
Mobiles.Description:
He is a specially trained warrior belonging to the military order of the
Faith.  His duty is to protect the faithful from persecution and infidel attacks
and his religious devotion combined with his superior skill makes him a deadly
opponent.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An assassin is guarding the entrance.
Mobiles.Description:
He is a thief who has specialized in killing others as effectively as
possible, using all sorts of weapons.  His superior knowledge of how and where
to use them combined with his extraordinary stealth makes him a deadly opponent.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A knight is guarding the entrance.
Mobiles.Description:
He is an expert warrior who has attained knighthood through countless
chivalrous deeds.  His duty is to protect the Guild of Swordsmen and his extreme
skill combined with his experience in warfare makes him a deadly opponent.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A bartender watches you calmly, while he skillfully mixes a drink.
Mobiles.Description: A tired looking Bartender who hates trouble in his bar.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A waiter is going around from one place to another.
Mobiles.Description: A tired looking waiter.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A man now leads a quiet, peaceful life as a waiter is standing here.
Mobiles.Description:
This man was obviously a famous sorcerer in his younger days as you instantly
recognize his face.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A waiter who seems to have reached contact with his God is standing here.
Mobiles.Description:
This waiter almost makes you feel like you should drop to your knees and
begin to worship your God.  Naaah.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A waiter who knows where all his customers keep their money is standing here.
Mobiles.Description: Hmmm...  Wonder where he got that coin he is playing with.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A waiter is here.
Mobiles.Description:
This guy looks like he could easily kill you while still carrying quite a few
firebreathers.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Filthy is standing here, eager to serve you a special drink.
Mobiles.Description:
Filthy looks real, ehm, dirty.  He likes to keep his customers happy, but do
not mess with him or else he'll get upset.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A Peacekeeper is standing here, ready to jump in at the first sign of trouble.
Mobiles.Description: He looks very strong and wise.  Looks like he doesn't answer to ANYONE.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A cityguard stands here.
Mobiles.Description: A big, strong, helpful, trustworthy guard.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A janitor is walking around, cleaning up.
Mobiles.Description: What a tough job he has.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beastly fido is mucking through the garbage looking for food here.
Mobiles.Description:
The fido is a small dog that has a foul smell and pieces of rotted meat
hanging around his teeth.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A mercenary is waiting for a job here.
Mobiles.Description: He looks pretty mean, and you imagine he'd do anything for money.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A singing, happy Drunk.
Mobiles.Description: A drunk who seems to be too happy, and to carry too much money.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beggar is here, asking for a few coins.
Mobiles.Description: The beggar looks like she is fed up with life.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An odif yltsaeb is here, walking backwards.
Mobiles.Description: The odif is a small god that has been reversed by some dog.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A cityguard is here, guarding the gate.
Mobiles.Description: A big, strong, helpful, trustworthy guard.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An oozing green gelatinous blob is here, sucking in bits of debris.
Mobiles.Description: A horrid looking thing; it is huge, greenish, and looks like the blob.

Mobiles.LongDescription: There is a Pet Shop Boy standing here cuddling something furry in his hands.
Mobiles.Description: As you look at him, he opens his hands to reveal a rat!

Mobiles.LongDescription: A small loyal kitten is here.
Mobiles.Description: The kitten looks like a cute, little, fierce fighter.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A small loyal puppy is here.
Mobiles.Description: The puppy looks like a cute, little, fierce fighter.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A small, quick, loyal beagle is here.
Mobiles.Description: The beagle looks like a fierce fighter.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A large, loyal rottweiler is here.
Mobiles.Description: The rottweiler looks like a strong, fierce fighter.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A large, trained wolf is here.
Mobiles.Description: The wolf looks like a strong, fearless fighter.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The cryogenicist is here, playing with a canister of liquid nitrogen.
Mobiles.Description:
You notice a tired look in her face.  She looks like she isn't paid well
enough to put up with any crap from mud players with attitudes.
